For example, in some West African villages, girls are often given honey in order to delay sexual development (1). Another instance of contraceptive methods used to deter sexual activities of females was found during a survey in Nigeria in a group of non-Guinean migrants from Cameroon. Nearly 10% reported using contraceptives in order to delay pregnancy following unprotected sex.
Child molestation conflict of law, 28th Nov 2010

Syrian women migrants report frequent cases of sexual exploitation in Germany, including beatings and cruel treatment. Out of 100 Sudanese women migrants all but 10 were victims of physical abuse, which could lead to deep traumas in many of them. Sex for profit exchange (a disguised variety of prostitution) also goes on in some countries of the EU and at least once sex trafficking was reported within the Mediterranean Co-operative Group of Gambian women migrants. For their former way of life most Gambians are geographically poorly adapted and may well be forced into extreme poverty in the EU.
